DIP server

General notes

API for
- iOS app
- Web app

Config header:
- jsonerror: true -> return error as json format.
Example: 


{
  "status": 401,
  "code": "UNAUTHORIZED",
  "details": "Unauthorized"
}


If jsonerror false, return "UNAUTHORIZED".
- In request, add debug = 1 to watch error trace.
Example: http://localhost:3000/auth/fblogin?debug=1


P/S: Some APIs are not used in current version, so I skipped response example for them.

API detail

1. Log in - Sign up

POST /auth/signup

Sign up by email

  • HTTP
  • Curl
POST /auth/signup HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:3000
Content-Type: application/json
jsonerror: true

{
    "email": "minh.nguyen@cofoundervp.com",
    "gender": "female",
    "password": "MinhMinh123",
    "firstName": "Minh",
    "role": "user",
    "code": "4cf82b00"
}

curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "jsonerror: true" -d '{
    "email": "minh.nguyen@cofoundervp.com",
    "gender": "female",
    "password": "MinhMinh123",
    "firstName": "Minh",
    "role": "user",
    "code": "4cf82b00"
}
' "http://localhost:3000/auth/signup"
  • SUCCESS
  • EMAIL_EXISTED
  • INVALID_INVITE_CODE
  • INVALID_PASSWORD

POST auth/login

Login by email

  • HTTP
  • Curl
POST /auth/login HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:3000
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic Og==
jsonerror: true

{"username": "minh.nguyen@cofoundervp1.com", "password": "MinhMinh123"}
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "Authorization: Basic Og==" -H "jsonerror: true" -d '{"username": "minh.nguyen@cofoundervp1.com", "password": "MinhMinh123"}' "http://localhost:3000/auth/login"

2. Resources (hotels, events)

GET /resources

Use to get list published hotels, events of DIP (cascade page). Very important. Display image: imageUrl + "_resized"

  • HTTP
  • Curl
GET /resources?location=los_angeles&searchKey=S&longitude=-80.1310856&latitude=25.7819332 HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:3000
Authorization: JWT eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzY29wZXMiOlsiYWxsIl0sImp0aSI6IjVGMlhaWk5vTUhxbHFDUWJpeEhEdjhHOHJYZFNFNGhxS1hBWThDcUFhalNJZFZObWF4d3ZaRmdWVm83cUREVGEiLCJpYXQiOjE0ODAwNzY1NTcsImV4cCI6MTQ4MDk0MDU1NywiaXNzIjoiZGlwIiwic3ViIjoiNTc2MGNiMzlmYTAyNzAzYjFjZDEyNDY1In0.aHp95WdzyYq4DfIYXZblRyH0QkbdhDJVJQawpHd5jMg
Content-Type: application/json
jsonerror: true

4. Payment

POST /hooks/subscriptionscreated

Stripe hook. We're using monthly membership. Every month, Stripe will charge by credit card of DIP subscribers, then Stripe will call this API to update status of these subscribers.

  • HTTP
  • Curl

Host: localhost:3000
Authorization: JWT eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzY29wZXMiOlsiYWxsIl0sImp0aSI6IjVGMlhaWk5vTUhxbHFDUWJpeEhEdjhHOHJYZFNFNGhxS1hBWThDcUFhalNJZFZObWF4d3ZaRmdWVm83cUREVGEiLCJpYXQiOjE0ODAwNzY1NTcsImV4cCI6MTQ4MDk0MDU1NywiaXNzIjoiZGlwIiwic3ViIjoiNTc2MGNiMzlmYTAyNzAzYjFjZDEyNDY1In0.aHp95WdzyYq4DfIYXZblRyH0QkbdhDJVJQawpHd5jMg
Content-Type: application/json
jsonerror: true

{
    "type": ""
}

POST GET Stripe token

Client call this API to get Stripe token, then use this token to add credit card to DIP server.

  • HTTP
  • Curl
POST /v1/tokens HTTP/1.1
Host: api.stripe.com
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

card[number]=4012888888881881&card[cvc]=123&card[exp_month]=12&card[exp_year]=2020&key=pk_test_TyfqkIPpt1CVJtUdsKlBCqYO
